data.Notes (optional): I believe it is imperative that we fight for our future, humans as a species have caused mass destruction, and thus far have acted as a virus to the earth, simply using resources until either the host (earth) or the virus (us) dies. We cannot carry on in this way, as Greta said, our metaphorical house is on fire, nobody wants to hear this, and the few that do in politics seem to only want to for their own political gain and popularity, yet we should fight on never the less. They push us down yet we will fight back, not with violence, but in civil unrest, we shall not pacify ourselves and be docile and obedient to the mouthpieces that sign our deathwarrant, revolution does not come from following the rules, and the rules are the very things choking us anyways. When we are burning, drowning, and choking on ash, they will listen, but until they can see their children physically caughing up blood in hellfire they wont, unless we do all we can to pre warn and change their minds, even if unsuccessful, we must try. They don't deserve our help, but they need it as we need theirs.

data.Notes (optional): Um 12 Uhr wird es in der Neustädter Hof- und Stadtkirche (Rote Reihe 3) eine öffentliche Andacht zum Thema Schöpfung geben, zu der mit Glockengeläut eingeladen wird. „Wir setzen ein Zeichen, wenn wir am 20. September für Andachten die Glocken läuten und damit einen Beitrag leisten, den Protest weithin hörbar zu machen,“ sagt Landesbischof Meister, der auch am Sternmarsch in Hannover und der Abschlusskundgebung am Trammplatz teilnehmen wird. ****** At 12 o'clock in the Neustädter Hof- und Stadtkirche (Red Row 3) there will be a public devotion on the subject of Creation, to which bells will be invited. 'We set a signal when we ring the bells for devotions on 20 September and thus make a contribution to making the protest audible,' says Regional Bishop Meister, who will also take part in the Sternmarsch in Hanover and the final rally at Trammplatz.

data.Notes (optional): Australia brenner. Et område på størrelse med Danmark er svidd av, over 1000 hjem er brent ned. 24 mennesker og 1,25 milliarder dyr er drept. Forskerne er tydelige - dette skyldes klimaendringene. Vi har ikke tid til å sitte stille lenger, vi trenger klimahandling NÅ! Jo lenger vi venter, jo flere og verre vil katastrofene bli. Men lederne våre fortsetter i stedet å helle bensin på bålet. Erna og Sylvi åpnet nettopp Johan Sverdrup, et oljefelt som skal pumpe olje lenge etter verden må være fornybar. Til og med i de sårbare økosystemene i Australbukta skal Equinor borre etter olje! Dette holder ikke mål! Norge må slutte å skape en brennende verden! 17. januar streiker australske aktivister for klima. Bli med oss å krev klimahandling i solidaritet med dem. Sees klokken 11 ved bypaviljongen!

data.Notes (optional): Hi there! I'm Barbara, I represent a Contemporary Dance Company here in Brazil, called Núcleo Contemporâneo Eliane Fetzer. We are a group of artists, that want to do much more than just dance. We want to use our  art to help and support causes. And so, our newest work, called 'Para Onde Foram as Andorinhas' (Where Did the Swallows go), brings a report about all that's been rappening about the fires in Amazonia, the climate changes, the death of indigenous people and animals that live on the forests, among other important things. We want and need this to be more than just a show for entertainment, and become a way to aware more people about the subject.I apreciate the atention.

data.Notes (optional): Red Rocks Initiatives for Sustainable Development is a non-profit organization operating in Africa. We work with individuals and groups to encourage, support, and celebrate more sustainable actions. From creating awareness of Global warming crisis, ending the use of plastic seed bags, preserving our natural resources and cultural heritage with the purpose of promoting tourism and environmental conservation as the leading sustainable community empowerment tool to uplift the socio economic status of the locals. Our organization does not only provide an opportunity for travelers to volunteer in Africa ’s most coveted destinations but also provides invaluable research opportunities for academia which include fellowship placements with sustainable-focused projects  across Africa , providing opportunities for hands-on learning and service. Our educational trips for students and young professionals make them learn about critical environmental issues and they contribute to create solutions across Africa. We welcome everyone to join and share their actions working together to increase examples of well-managed sustainable tourism and environmental conservation to uplift Africans out of poverty and instill them a sense of purpose and pride.

data.Notes (optional): AWARA has stood in the forefront of nature & river conservation since its inception in 2013.  Originally as Nature Walkers India, AWARA walker-runner-volunteers cleared hundreds of tonnes of trash dumped on the river bed & carved a nature trail along that trained scores of middle & long distance runners, marathoners, some from slumkids & others from deprived backgrounds.  Such activity spurned away hordes of open defecators, waste dumpers, sand-miners, drug peddlars, vandals & other criminal elements off the river precinct. data.Notes (optional): We demand urgent action. Help us by supporting and joining the millions across the globe taking action and bringing awareness to our ongoing climate crisis. We want Sakskatchewan to be apart of the bigger conversation about what we can do too. We as a unified community wish to bring awareness to our rising global crisis through a peaceful climate demonstration in front of the La Ronge Town Hall slotted on Friday October 11th, 2019 at 12:00 PM – 3 PM.People across the globe are experiencing its effects. Intense rainstorms, severe droughts, extreme heat waves, flooding, the destruction of homes, communities, natural spaces etc. Even the most vulnerable to these effects are among us: our children, our elders and the less fortunate. They are all in danger of increasing cold, heat stress and pollution. Yet, we avert our eyes. Because well…it isn’t affecting us too much? Wrong. The effects of climate change are very real, and this is even happening in our own backyard. Fires, flooding, insane windstorms, intense weather that have been ongoing the past few years. None like we’ve ever seen before, yet it’ll only get worse if we say and do nothing. We need to stop averting our eyes and face what is happening, even in remote communities. What do we want to do about it? We want to take a stance and bring awareness to the world and humanity’s biggest threat. From our government we want to demand action. We want to demand reform for its criminal inaction on our ecological crisis. We want to ask for honesty, responsibility and courage to face our climate crisis head-on. We want to plead with our leaders to stop basing decisions on economic growth and take immediate action by listening to the climate and biodiversity data accumulated over the last 30 years. Plead to pay attention now, before it’s too late. On a community-level we want to start a conversation about what we can do. Introducing the idea of cracking down on pollutants in our community with the usage of cleaner energy. Introducing more local farming and supporting the food banks and schools in their effort for a cleaner community through their gardens, stricter regulations on pollution. also seeking the support of local businesses to follow in the footsteps of businesses taking more sustainable routes such as Cravings etc. We no longer want to sit around and wait for slow change, we as students want to step up against this bystander effect circulating and this ignored crisis. Climate change is affecting our community, our future, your children’s children and so much more. We want to ask for change now before it’s too late. As a unified group of people, we want to make a difference by bringing awareness, inspire deeper discussion about what we can change. Show people that change can come from the will of the people, our citizens.

This particular video really opened my eyes on the systemic collapse of the thermo-industrial civilization.https://lnkd.in/eyMuaEBAccording to a new report from IBM Marketing Cloud 2017 90% of the data in the world today has been created in the last two years alone, at 2.5 quintillion bytes of data a day!Smart Cities are a good start for 'Upgrading'. We must start analyzing the data all around us with the help of AI. To be able to efficiently analyze the overwhelming amount of data with real-time analysis. With the help of progress in new technologies like Graphene processors/Quantum Gates. processing the information is getting easier and combined with new insights on the bizarre behavior of rotating bodies (intermediate axis theorem) and the understanding of the Brain. We Will 'Unlock' new exciting things in the New Era of Autonomous MachinesEventually, data analysis from multiple smart cities will enable us to allocate resources efficiently. Giving us a chance for a prosperous futureTime to 'level up' before its 'game over.'SpanishBasta ya! Despierta ! Es hora de cambiar la mentalidad egoísta , por mucho tiempo hemos operado y trabajado con gran determinación de conseguir rentabilidad máxima para nuestro personal beneficio, dejando de lado el bienestar común del resto de la sociedad; el hecho de que sabemos conscientemente la existencia de prácticas injustas y poco éticas e ignorando el echo de que moralmente es un deber de todos nosotros encontrar soluciones para que esto no siga ocurriendo. Junto con Greta los invito y exhorto a compartir este mensaje que es tan importante hoy por hoy, es tiempo de despertar! Veo personas haciendo memes de nuestro presidente Sebastián Piñera en la ONU sin ningún aporte real más allá de la burla a este personaje ....y hoy quiero decirles a todos y en especial a estas personas que según cálculos y estadísticas hechas el punto de “No retorno” se aproxima exponencialmente....estamos a tiempo gente de mi amado país ! Dejemos ya de vivir en esta mediocre realidades burlándose de de otras personas y empecemos a darnos cuenta que estamos en un lugar donde solo miramos hacia atrás por miedo al futuro! Yo estoy cansado y he tomado la decision de actuar y tomar mi destino en mis manos como futuro ingeniero en 2020. Tendré el gran desafío de aportar con mi conocimiento enfocado a el area de inteligencia artificial y la creación de ciudades inteligentes que sean eco- friendly , para proteger nuestra naturaleza o más bien de lo que va quedando de ella .... despertemos juntos para progresar sin destruir nuestro medio ambiente , estoy enfocado en desarrollar tecnologías para evidenciar el mal uso de recursos e alocar de forma óptima e menos destructivas para que todos los seres que habitan el planeta podamos coexistir en armonía ! No solo para el beneficio de la raza humana .Lo as pensado?  Con que cara les diremos a nuestros hijos que destruimos todo lo hermoso de la naturaleza , cuando les mostremos fotos de hermosas especies de animales que estarán ya extintos por nuestra culpa por la avariciosa ansia de tener y poder sin importar que destruimos ....y qué diremos cuando nos pregunten porque no hicimos nada ? por eso te pido hoy reflexionar y unirte a este movimiento apóyame y juntos reconstruyamos como millennials lo que nuestras pasadas generaciones destruyeron tan descaradamente !@cop25cl votemos por la gente.Very fascinated with AI and interested in Innovative technologies and tools like high-performance computing, deep learning, machine learning, inference, visualization, smart cities, medical imaging, and IoT. I have a wide array of knowledge from experimenting AI solutions for specific expert systems like predicting stocks, generating images, reconstructing images, sentiment analysis, lung detection illnesses, making smart solutions for Smart Cities like smart parking, anomaly detection and more between a few. IntelliScan a project in which I'm particularly proud of that uses transfer learning for training a model, that to my surprise was with a rather small data set form Keggle. On the other hand, I've demonstrated the ability to convey technical topics to clients and have been recognized for my exemplary record of accomplishment to establish and maintain productive work environments and relationships.Smart Cities are key to Humanity as a whole. Today the thought of creating True Ai is not a question of 'if' but of 'when'. This is because technology and understanding of the brain are evolving so rapidly. together these developments will enable us to create computers that can think and learn independently. It's pretty hard to predict the future that awaits us with 100% accuracy at least based on observation of trends and technology today we could make predictions for tomorrow take Moore's law for example. especially with GPUs, graphene processors, and quantum gates are around the corner. some more than others... Yes. Smart Cities are an excellent way to unleash the true power of AI and impact humanity just like the discovery of fire impacted our ancestors. I like to think about this era like the 'The Fourth Age' or 'Life 3.0'. Without a doubt, the future is in our hands and we must strive for progress if we want to persist throughout timeIn the future, I see myself able to oversee mayor software developments to make an impact of the usage of uprising technologies especially Artificial intelligence, essentially upgrading humanity as we know it. Eventually, the adoption of these new technologies in today's digital transformation will not only be a matter of life or death for the big enterprises but for all humanity and the Planet.PD: I'm starting a cigarrilos4ClimateChange movement for University students And giving away biodegradable trash bags with a message about, the implications of internal change and love. data.Notes (optional): Rockwool’s proposed factory in Ranson, WV would be a climate disaster- the kind of facility that should no longer be built anywhere if we want to preserve our climate for future generations!  The plant would burn around 90 tons of coal and 1.6 million cubic feet of fracked gas per day.  It would emit 156 thousand tons of harmful pollutants per year.  The site is located just across the road from a Title 1 elementary school.  In spite of this, Rockwool, the Danish insulation manufacturer, claims to be a “Green” company.  Please join me and Eastern Panhandle Green Coalition every Friday as we peacefully protest this company near the entrance to the site.  The location is at the intersection of Northport Avenue and the Route 9 Bike Path, in Ranson, WV.  We will gather from 11am till 1pm, starting on January 17th, 2020 and continuing until Rockwool agrees to either leave or go Zero Emissions at its factory.
